<section id="datenbank">
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3147102" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="CHG" oldref="1"><link href="text/shared/main0212.xhp" name="Database Bar">Table Data Bar</link></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3146117" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="2">The <emph>Table Data</emph> bar is located at the top of the data source view.<comment>UFI: cannot see it. changed following the spec doc specs.openoffice.org/appwide/toolbars/Toolbar_content_spec.sxw</comment><comment>UFI: bar has no name in m58</comment></paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3153394" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="10">Use the sort and filter icons to control the data view. The original database table is not modified by changes in the data view.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3149346" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="12">The modified data view is stored until you change or cancel the sorting or filtering criteria. If a filter is active, the <emph>Apply Filter</emph> icon on the Table Data bar is activated.</paragraph>
